data.name: richTextBoxStreamCommand.Text
data.value:
This is experimental feature. In the field above enter the link from IP stream; it can be: - IP camera video stream from Internet or local network, - streaming service link (audio or video), - Internet radio stream,
How to use it: 1. Enter link 2. Check stream to ensure it exists 3. Check Live streaming to see how does it look and/or sounds 4. Select Save file where it will be saved 5. Start recording 6. When you want to stop recording, just close the separate FFmpeg window that will be opened
During recording you can perform other tasks, or even start new recording. Separate window will be opened for each new stream.
If you choose audio file (MP3, AAC, OGG....) it will be saved in in 1 file. If you choose video file (MP4, MKV, etc) it will be saved in more files, each 60 seconds long. To change this, EDIT THE COMMAND MANUALLY!!!
BEFORE CLICKING "Start Recording", COMMAND MAY BE EDITED MANUALLY.
